```

## Deliverables

1. **Core Alert Engine**
   - `src/services/alerts/AlertEngine.ts`
   - `src/services/alerts/AlertRule.ts`
   - `src/services/alerts/AlertManager.ts`
   - Type definitions for alerts

2. **Push Notification System**
   - `public/sw.js` (service worker)
   - `src/services/notifications/PushNotification.ts`
   - `src/hooks/useNotifications.ts`
   - Permission management UI

3. **Email Service**
   - `src/services/notifications/EmailService.ts`
   - Email templates in `src/templates/emails/`
   - Email configuration interface

4. **SMS Service**
   - `src/services/notifications/SMSService.ts`
   - Phone verification component
   - SMS provider integration

5. **Alert Configuration UI**
   - `src/components/alerts/AlertRuleBuilder.tsx`
   - `src/components/alerts/AlertHistory.tsx`
   - `src/pages/notifications/AlertSettings.tsx`

6. **API Endpoints**
   - `POST /api/alerts/rules` - Create alert rule
   - `GET /api/alerts/rules` - List alert rules
   - `POST /api/alerts/test` - Send test alert
   - `GET /api/alerts/history` - Alert history

## Technical Requirements

### Alert Rule Conditions
- Strategy performance thresholds
- System health metrics
- API response times
- Error rate monitoring
- Custom metric alerts

### Notification Features
- Rich push notifications with actions
- Scheduled delivery windows
- Alert grouping and bundling
- Multi-language support
- Accessibility compliance

### Performance
- Alert processing latency < 100ms
- Push notification delivery < 1s
- Email delivery < 30s
- SMS delivery < 5s
- Alert history retention 90 days

## Acceptance Criteria

### Browser Push Notifications
- [ ] Users receive real-time push notifications in browser
- [ ] Notifications include actionable buttons
- [ ] Permission requests are handled gracefully
- [ ] Offline notifications are queued and delivered
- [ ] Custom notification sounds and icons

### Email Alerts
- [ ] HTML emails render correctly on all clients
- [ ] Email templates are customizable
- [ ] Bounce and unsubscribe handling
- [ ] Rate limiting prevents spam
- [ ] Test email functionality

### SMS Alerts
- [ ] Critical alerts delivered via SMS
- [ ] Phone number verification
- [ ] Message length optimization
- [ ] International number support
- [ ] Delivery status tracking

### Alert Rule Configuration
- [ ] Visual rule builder with drag-and-drop
- [ ] Support for complex logical conditions
- [ ] Rule validation and testing
- [ ] Import/export alert rules
- [ ] Rule versioning

### Integration
- [ ] Alerts triggered by strategy events
- [ ] System health monitoring
- [ ] Custom webhook support
- [ ] Third-party integrations (Slack, Teams)
- [ ] API for external alert sources

## Dependencies

1. **WebSocket Module** (Task 004) - For real-time alert delivery
2. **User Preferences** (Task 005) - For notification settings
3. **Monitoring Dashboard** (Task 006) - For alert triggers
4. **Browser Push API** - For native notifications
5. **Email/SMS Providers** - External service integration

## Testing Requirements

### Unit Tests
- Alert rule evaluation logic
- Notification channel delivery
- Template rendering
- Permission management

### Integration Tests
- End-to-end alert flow
- Cross-channel delivery
- Rate limiting
- Quiet hours enforcement

### E2E Tests
- Alert creation workflow
- Notification reception
- Alert acknowledgment
- Configuration management

## Success Metrics

1. **Alert Latency**: < 100ms from trigger to processing
2. **Delivery Rate**: > 99.5% for push notifications
3. **Email Delivery**: > 98% within 30 seconds
4. **SMS Delivery**: > 95% within 5 minutes
5. **User Engagement**: > 80% alerts acknowledged within 1 hour

## Notes

- Consider privacy regulations for notification data
- Implement graceful degradation for unsupported browsers
- Plan for internationalization of alert messages
- Ensure GDPR compliance for email/SMS communications